 Keywords: Tobacco; Malawi; Plot size; Farming-based finance; Cost (wasting very little while working or producing something) 
 
 1. Introduction 
 Improvement in the (wasting very little while working or producing something) of farming-based production, including working well growth, is an very important part of any (away from cities) growth plan. In 
 sub-Saharan Africa, where price-based (change to make better/related to changing something) 
 policies have not led to broad-based money-based growth, 
 gain in the (wasting very little while working or producing something) of farming-based production is 
 viewed as necessary for money-based growth and the 
 help of (away from cities) poorness. (away from cities) finance may add/give by helping the (instance of buying something for money) of expensive inputs and 
