 of well being. Diagne and Zeller (200 1) argue that 
 such independence may be necessary in the face of 
 the (not working properly) of (away from cities) maize markets, caused by 
 a lack of marketable extra of maize in smallholdings 
 and an not enough transportation (set of machines). So, 
